      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Telegram spooled buffered replay",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fix Telegram spooled replay so buffered/deferred message processing keeps ownership of the update lifecycle until final reply dispatch settles.\n- Keep retryable buffered dispatch failures pending in the ingress spool without advancing the Telegram update watermark or leaving stale claims.\n- Add focused coverage for deferred spooled participants, same-lane buffering, retryable failures, timeout handling, and dedupe cleanup.\n\nFixes #92129\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/bot-message.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/polling-session.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/memory-host-events.test.ts`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `$autoreview` clean before commit\n- AWS Crabbox live Telegram fix proof: `run_b62d06ee011a`, lease `cbx_7a4380b42748`, provider `aws`, exit `0`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Telegram isolated-ingress spooled replay no longer acknowledges or cleans up a live update before buffered final dispatch settles.\n\nReal environment tested: AWS Crabbox Linux (`cbx_7a4380b42748`) using Convex-leased `telegram` kind credentials for live driver/SUT Telegram bots. No `telegram-user` credential was leased.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Started a live Telegram polling session from this branch with isolated ingress enabled, sent a real driver-bot group message to the SUT bot, forced `dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher` to throw `LIVE_PROOF_DISPATCH_FAILURE`, then inspected the product Telegram ingress spool, claims, and persisted update watermark.\n\nEvidence after fix: `OPENCLAW_92129_LIVE_FIX_PROOF={\"status\":\"pass\",\"marker\":\"OPENCLAW-92129-LIVE-1781218662647-06g4j5\",\"sentMessageId\":20593,\"spooledUpdateId\":785090139,\"pendingIds\":[785090139],\"claimIds\":[],\"dispatchCalls\":13,\"persistedUpdateIds\":[]}`\n\nObserved result after fix: The live Telegram update remains pending for retry, has no stuck claim, dispatch failure is exercised, and the update id is not persisted.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full repository CI is pending on this PR.\n",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-spooled-buffered-replay",
